@Node "doitvcr"
@title "SCART-VCR cable"

What you need:
Amiga monitor (1084 or 8033 or something like that)
Vga monitor   (I have a "AST SVGA-LR")
VCR           (With SCART)
RF-cable      (You got one with your amiga)
@{"SCART-cable" LINK "cable"}  (Depending of 1084-model)

How to connect:
1. Connect the VGA-monitor with a vga-adapter to the video port (as usual).
2. Connect the RF-cable from your amiga to the VCR.
3. Connect a @{"SCART-cable" LINK "cable"} from the video to you 1084.
4. Put your monitor in Comp.-mode (small swith on the 1084-monitor)
5. Tune VCR to amiga-signal.

@{i}Return to @{ui}@{"main" LINK "main"}.
@EndNode

@Node "Switch"
@title "How do I switch?"

If you want VGA then turn on your VGA-monitor (and turn of your 1084!)
if you want 1084 then turn on your 1084 (and turn of your VGA-monitor!)

Now I use the VGA for "serious"-work and the 1084 for games!

