@Node "comp"
@title "Composite-cable"

What you need:
Amiga monitor   (1084 or 8033 or something like that)
Vga monitor     (I have a "AST SVGA-LR")
Composite cable (Ordinary cabel with a 'phono' contact in each end)

Connect one end to amiga video-out and the other end to monitor video-in.

You can try this with the monitor soud cabel if you like. Put the red one
in amiga video-out and the other red one in monitor video-in (Or use the
black ones if you like them better...).

Put your monitor in Comp.-mode (small swith on the 1084-monitor)

This connection should give you the best picture-quality but the
VCR-connection has the benifit of alowing you to watch TV on your monitor
as well.

Why not take a look at Pietro Altomani project "15khz_vga.txt" on aminet?

@{i}Return to @{ui}@{"main" LINK "main"}.
@Endnode

@Node "scartvideo"
@title "SCART to Video"

If your 1084 doesn't have a scart-input then build a special cable
that connects to videoin (I did this):
SCART:			1084s:
19	CVBS OUT	Videoin
17	CVBS GND	GND Videoin 
1	AUDIO OUT	Audioin R (or if it was L, I doesn't remember..)
3	AUDIO OUT	Audioin L (or if it was R...)
4	AUDIO GND	GND Audio (R or L)

@{i}Return to @{ui}@{"main" LINK "main"}.
@Endnode

